the land: Houbigant contends, that, instead of haaretz, "the land," we
should read haaron, "the ark;" for the ו, wav, and ן, noon final, might
easily be mistaken for ץ, tzadday final; which is the only difference
between the two words. This conjecture is the more likely, as the next
verse tells us, that Micah's graven image continued at Dan "all the time
that the house of God was at Shiloh;" which was till the ark was taken
by the Philistines.

